article.headline: Cheatham's double-double helps Akron beat Ohio, 83-68
article.linkText: Cheatham's double-double helps Akron beat Ohio, 83-68
article.story: AKRON, Ohio -- Kwan Cheatham Jr. scored 17 points and grabbed 13 rebounds for his third double-double this season and four starters reached double digits as Akron raced past Ohio 83-68 on Tuesday night, pushing its win streak to eight games. Isaiah Johnson and Jimond Ivey scored 15 points each for the Zips (15-3, 5-0 Mid-American Conference), and Antino Jackson tossed in 11 with three 3-pointers. The win was Akron's 26th in a row at James A. Rhodes Arena, third longest in Division I. Jaaron Simmons scored 19 points to lead the Bobcats, who trailed 38-35 after a half. Gavin Block scored to start the second half as Ohio (11-5, 3-2) came within two points, but Cheatham hit a jumper, Ivey dunked and Johnson added a layup to kick off a 22-10 run. Ohio didn't get closer than 12 points over the final 11 minutes. Akron shot 55 percent (31-56) with nine 3-pointers.
